org.gradoop.dataintegration.transformation

Class EdgeToVertex

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.dataintegration.transformation.EdgeToVertex
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Operator, UnaryBaseGraphToBaseGraphOperator<LogicalGraph>, UnaryBaseGraphToValueOperator<LogicalGraph,LogicalGraph>, UnaryGraphToGraphOperator

    public class EdgeToVertex
extends Object
implements UnaryGraphToGraphOperator
    For edges of a specific label this graph transformation creates a new vertex containing the properties of the edge and two new edges respecting the direction of the original edge. The newly created edges and vertex labels are user-defined.

    The original edges are still part of the resulting graph. Use a FilterFunction on the original label to remove them.

                    String newVertexLabel,

        The constructor for the structural transformation.
        Parameters:
        edgeLabel - The label of the edges use for the transformation. (No edges will be transformed if this parameter is null).
        newVertexLabel - The label of the newly created vertex.
        edgeLabelSourceToNew - The label of the newly created edge which points to the newly created vertex.
        edgeLabelNewToTarget - The label of the newly created edge which starts at the newly created vertex.
